title: Plate, Etching, 1889
provenance: A present for the tenth wedding anniversary of Mr. and Mrs. George T. Bliss, February 12, 1889.
description: Sheet metal. On one side, engraved script reading "Feb. 12, 1879-1889". Reverse, plan. Corners cut at angle of 45 degrees. Small punched hole with yellowed ribbon in upper left corner.

tombstone.epitaph:
Plate, Etching, 1889.
1889. Plate, etching. Gift of Anonymous Donor. 1937-45-5-a.
